      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHASING APHRODITE (2) was solid fresh last start over 2000m at Flemington, finishing ninth, beaten 5 lengths. Has a very good second up record and looks ideally placed here. Expected to improve sharply. REGAL LION (1) wasn't disgraced in city class last time when finishing sixth at Flemington. This is easier and will take running down. THE MIGHTY SPAR (4) hasn't been far away lately, beaten 1.2 lengths at his most recent outing when fourth over 2000m in the Colac Cup. Goes well third-up, placed only trey here and bold run is likely. CABLE DANCER (6) was always well back last start at the first run of this campaign and never threatened, finishing ninth over 1600m at Caulfield Heath. Strips fitter and has a strong record this longer journey. Should be in the finish. STATION ONE (3) is a speedy type who will take running down.",
